moral_action: Tony declines to take a drink with his colleague, and lets him know that he would enjoy a drink after work, but not during his shift.

norm: It's frowned upon to drink at work.
immoral_action: Tony decides that one drink won't hurt anything, so he accepts the drink he has been offered.

norm: It's good to pay attention to your host.
moral_action: Leah asks the boy she's interested in how he knows the host, sparking a three-way conversation that includes the boy she's interested in.

norm: It's good to pay attention to your host.
immoral_action: Leah ignores the friend that just walked up and instead tries to start a side conversation with the boy she's interested in.

norm: You shouldn't be with someone you don't have feelings for.
moral_action: Dan realizes he can't find a date so quickly, so he asks a friend to join him.

norm: You shouldn't be with someone you don't have feelings for.
immoral_action: Dan asks Tina, who likes him and will agree to go to the event, even though he doesn't like her.

norm: It is not okay to laugh at others.
moral_action: Tina offers to help Samantha clean the dress up and to borrow her extra change of clothes.

norm: It is not okay to laugh at others.
immoral_action: Tina tries to tell Samantha a joke to cheer her up about how it looks like she rolled in the mud, and laughs heartily at it.

norm: You're discouraged from bragging about your possessions.
moral_action: Ace mentions that he got a nice new car and asks his friends what cars they like.

norm: You're discouraged from bragging about your possessions.
immoral_action: Ace tells his friends about his car and goes over every detail of its luxury features.

norm: It is good to communicate with family
moral_action: Ian calls his family and asks when a good time would be for them to go to dinner.

norm: It is good to communicate with family
immoral_action: Ian keeps his arrival a surprise, shows up at their house, and invites them out to eat.

norm: It's wrong to pick on other people
moral_action: Jason introduces himself to Kyle and offers to show him around the campus.

norm: It's wrong to pick on other people
immoral_action: Jason approaches Kyle and sarcastically says, you can hide, but you can't run.

norm: You shouldn't break up your partner's friendships.
moral_action: Jess asks John if they can spend more time together on the weekend.

norm: You shouldn't break up your partner's friendships.
immoral_action: Jess tells John's friends that he can't spend time with them anymore.

norm: It's mean to hate someone's dog.
moral_action: Bob lets his neighbor know that he has been cleaning up after his dog and would appreciate if he would not have to do that.

norm: It's mean to hate someone's dog.
immoral_action: Bob tells his neighbor that he can't stand the dog and if he sees it around his yard again, he will call animal control to take it away.

norm: You should try to help your friends.
moral_action: Dan says he'll try to help his friend study for the test as best as he can.

norm: You should try to help your friends.
immoral_action: Dan says he won't help his friend with their exam because they're probably not going to pass the class regardless.

norm: You should always pay people the money you owe them
moral_action: Will decides to bring it up himself so that he can bring it up at a time in his life when paying it back would not hurt him.

norm: You should always pay people the money you owe them
immoral_action: Will stays quiet and hopes that either his friend won't bring it up or will get the amount wrong.

norm: You shouldn't say things that offended people
moral_action: Blake takes a breath and asks a worker if he has any fresh apples.

norm: You shouldn't say things that offended people
immoral_action: Blake says in a raised voice that the workers in the store can't do their jobs in front of a worker.

norm: It's good to spend time with people you care about
moral_action: Sophie makes sure to stay close with her family despite being in college because they have always been there for her.

norm: It's good to spend time with people you care about
immoral_action: Sophie thinks that socializing is what she needs to do and goes out every night trying her best to not be home if she doesn't have to be.

norm: It's mean to make someone feel worthless.
moral_action: John takes a breath, tells Mindy he lost his job and goes to work out.

norm: It's mean to make someone feel worthless.
immoral_action: John raises his voice and tells Mindy she can't cook, so she shouldn't even try.

norm: It's bad to blow up with anger at a parent.
moral_action: Justin explains to his father that he needs more help on his school work.

norm: It's bad to blow up with anger at a parent.
immoral_action: Justin starts to yell at his father and tell him that the bad grades were his father's fault.

norm: It's wrong to say racist words.
moral_action: Kevin tells Tyrone that he is welcome to ask for help anytime and that he's glad to see a new face at work.

norm: It's wrong to say racist words.
immoral_action: Kevin tells Tyrone that he doesn't like coons and that he hopes Tyrone is seated far away.

norm: You should help others in times of need.
moral_action: Kevin tells Peter that he would be glad to loan him money as long as Peter pays it back.

norm: You should help others in times of need.
immoral_action: Kevin tells Peter that he actually doesn't have any money at all, even though he has a healthy bank account, and that he can't help.

norm: It is not okay to insult someone's physical appearance.
moral_action: James tells Bill that he was once new too and would have appreciated some help back then, so if Bill needs anything he can ask.

norm: It is not okay to insult someone's physical appearance.
immoral_action: James tells Bill that right now he looks totally disgusting right now, so he should keep at it at the gym.

norm: It's good to inform your landlord of problems.
moral_action: Tom explains his work situation to his landlord, who agrees to allow Tom extra time to pay his rent over the coming months.

norm: It's good to inform your landlord of problems.
immoral_action: Tom starts selling weed to get money to pay his rent.

norm: You shouldn't be rude toward employees.
moral_action: Dave tells Phil that he notices Phil is having a hard time at work and offers to give Phil a coaching session.

norm: You shouldn't be rude toward employees.
immoral_action: Dave tells Phil that he is a moron and that his work habits are awful and that if he doesn't pick it up he's gone.

norm: It's frowned upon to tell people what to do.
moral_action: Wyatt tells Jody to drive safely and to have a great time out and about.

norm: It's frowned upon to tell people what to do.
immoral_action: Wyatt tells Jody she can't go because he doesn't want her spending their money and forbids her from leaving.

norm: You shouldn't trick someone into doing your chores.
moral_action: Paula tells her roommate she was invited for drinks and asks him to help her clean the house, so she can go out as soon as possible.

norm: You shouldn't trick someone into doing your chores.
immoral_action: Paula tells her roommate she is not feeling well and can't do the cleaning today, then quietly leaves the house while her roommate is doing the cleaning.

norm: It's good to help feed those dealing with food scarcity.
moral_action: Michael takes a portion of the extra canned goods that he has purchased to a local food bank and donates the food to help families in need.

norm: It's good to help feed those dealing with food scarcity.
immoral_action: Michael continues to cram food into his cupboards, pantry and even in the closets, until he has more than he could eat in a year's time.

norm: You shouldn't lie and tell people you have a cold.
moral_action: Tanya thanks her friends for the offer, but explains that she needs some time to relax after her long week.

norm: You shouldn't lie and tell people you have a cold.
immoral_action: Tanya tells her friends she can't make it because she's feeling ill.

norm: It's wrong to laugh at a suicide attempt.
moral_action: Luke tells Ken that he is really concerned about him and hopes Ken will let him find help for him.

norm: It's wrong to laugh at a suicide attempt.
immoral_action: Luke laughs heartily and tells Ken that he's a loser who can't even get suicide right and then keeps laughing.

norm: You shouldn't make fun of customers in your store.
moral_action: Shaun quietly asks his colleague if they would please help the elderly woman find what she is looking for, and Shaun would ring up her purchase.

norm: You shouldn't make fun of customers in your store.
immoral_action: Shaun points to the elderly woman and tells his colleague that she moves so slowly she will never find what she is looking for.

norm: It's mean to frequently leave your spouse alone at night.
moral_action: Damien works a few extra hours to help pay for a nurse to go and check on his mother every night.

norm: It's mean to frequently leave your spouse alone at night.
immoral_action: Damien goes and spends the night at his mother's house every night for over a month.

norm: You should respect peoples privacy.
moral_action: Alexia asks Raul what she can do to help, and then drops the subject when Raul says he doesn't want to talk about it.

norm: You should respect peoples privacy.
immoral_action: Alexia asks Raul repeatedly to tell them what's wrong, even though he's said he doesn't want to talk about it.

norm: It's wrong to be jealous of others in life.
moral_action: Janice supports Mary by asking questions about her new house and offering to help with the move if she needs any.

norm: It's wrong to be jealous of others in life.
immoral_action: Janice tells Mary that she'll never be able to keep a house that big clean and all that furniture she picked out will collect too much dust.

norm: It is wrong to withhold rent from a roommate.
moral_action: Rebekah gives the roommate her share of the rent money and works overtime to make money to pay for the concert tickets.

norm: It is wrong to withhold rent from a roommate.
immoral_action: Rebekah tells her roommate that she is going through a rough time and can't help pay the rent this month, but uses the money to buy tickets to the concert.

norm: It's bad to harass people.
moral_action: James approaches a woman and hands her a flyer, asking her to please read about the reason for the protest.

norm: It's bad to harass people.
immoral_action: James gets right in the face of a man walking down the street and starts screaming about his views and won't move when the man tries to leave.

norm: It is unacceptable to tease someone for making a mistake.
moral_action: Tony talks to his son about the importance of taking care of things and tells him he'll need to help pay to repair his bike.

norm: It is unacceptable to tease someone for making a mistake.
immoral_action: Tony makes fun of his son for leaving his bike out and laughs about how his son can't use it anymore.

norm: You shouldn't use people.
moral_action: Julie tells Pat that she needs a ride to work, would be very grateful for the help and offers to pay for gas.

norm: You shouldn't use people.
immoral_action: Julie asks her coworker Pat for a ride to work every day but doesn't offer to pay for gas or even thank her.

norm: It's wrong to hate people with disabilities.
moral_action: Dave tells Bill that he's glad to meet him and will try his hardest to show Bill he's a good officer.

norm: It's wrong to hate people with disabilities.
immoral_action: Dave tells Bill that he cannot take a man in a wheelchair seriously as a police officer since he can't even make an arrest in his condition.

norm: You shouldn't laugh at how people look
moral_action: Henry stops and talks to the man and offers to buy him some new clothing.

norm: You shouldn't laugh at how people look
immoral_action: Henry stops and tells the man that he looks disgusting and starts to laugh at him.

norm: It is kind to help your neighbors.
moral_action: Joe offers his help to start Ryan's lawnmower and is able to get it running.

norm: It is kind to help your neighbors.
immoral_action: Joe tells Ryan that it looks like he's not going to be able to mow his lawn today since his lawnmower won't start.

norm: It's good to tell people your opinions.
moral_action: Donna tells Leigh that the dress doesn't really compliment her skin tone and offers to help her find something better.

norm: It's good to tell people your opinions.
immoral_action: Donna tells Leigh that it looks great, but really thinks it doesn't look very nice on her.

norm: It's rude to hate on women.
moral_action: John takes a breath and tells Mindy it can be hard to get the salt amount just right in cooking and the rest of it tastes good.

norm: It's rude to hate on women.
immoral_action: John raises his voice and says in front of Mindy that women just can't cook.

norm: You shouldn't be against people of certain religions.
moral_action: Catherine explains the layout of the city, and she buys the family a map while talking to them.

norm: You shouldn't be against people of certain religions.
immoral_action: Catherine tells the man that she refuses to help someone with bad values before walking away.

norm: It's wrong to wish someone's relationship fails.
moral_action: Sean shows support for his friend's relationship and has a conversation with him about making sure they still find time to do things together.

norm: It's wrong to wish someone's relationship fails.
immoral_action: Sean never shows any enthusiasm for his friend's relationship hoping to will an end to it into existence, so he and his friend can spend more time together.
